Commentary Text: Chahal to Dhawan, out Caught by Washington Sundar!! Dhawan perishes after reaching his fifty. Boy! RCB needed that badly. Chahal as he ususally does for RCB, gets the wicket in the middle overs. Dhawan premeditates the sweep shot, Chahal saw that and he is astute enough to drag his length back and bowled well wide of off. It clipped his top-edge and Sundar takes a dolly at short fine leg. Dhawan has done his job though, over to Pant and Iyer now. Dhawan c Washington Sundar b Chahal 50(37) [4s-5 6s-2]

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Parthiv Patel!! Edged and gone! Oh, wait PP is down on his feet and the umpires decide to go upstairs. The soft signal is OUT! Commentary Text: Rutherford to de Villiers, out Caught by Axar!! Has this sealed the match for DC? A superb running catch at deep mid-wicket and yet another long hop has got them a wicket - this was short and AB rocked back on the pull, don't think he hit it all that well - Axar ran across from the deep, kept his eyes on the ball and then latched onto a fine overhead catch. The equation has just got tougher for the men in red. de Villiers c Axar b Rutherford 17(19) [6s-1]

A smart catch from Axar at backward point and Rabada can afford a smile now - much needed wicket for the Capitals - this was short and well wide of off, Parthiv made room and crunched the cut - didn't keep it down and didn't find the gap, straight to Axar who does well to hold on.
